  "prompt": "Top 10 website makers?",
  "response": "As of now, here are ten popular website builders that are widely used for creating websites:\n\n1. **Wix** - A user-friendly platform with a drag-and-drop interface, offering a wide range of templates and customization options.\n\n2. **Squarespace** - Known for its sleek, modern designs, Squarespace is ideal for creatives and businesses looking for visually appealing websites.\n\n3. **WordPress.com** - A versatile platform that caters to both bloggers and businesses, it offers extensive themes and plugins for customization.\n\n4. **WordPress.org** - The self-hosted version of WordPress allows for greater customization and flexibility, making it popular among developers.\n\n5. **Shopify** - A specialized website builder for eCommerce, Shopify provides tools to create and manage online stores easily.\n\n6. **Weebly** - Offers a simple drag-and-drop interface and is user-friendly for small businesses and personal websites.\n\n7. **Zyro** - A newer platform that combines AI tools with a clean interface to help users build websites quickly.\n\n8. **Webflow** - A more advanced option that allows for full design control, suitable for designers and developers who want a custom-coded feel.\n\n9. **GoDaddy Website Builder** - Known for its simplicity and integration with domain services, GoDaddy\u2019s builder is ideal for quick setups.\n\n10. **Jimdo** - An easy-to-use platform that allows users to create websites using AI, suitable for small businesses and personal projects.\n\nEach of these website builders has its strengths, depending on your specific needs such as eCommerce functionality, design customization, or blogging capabilities.",
